  "title": "Resident Engineer - Coastal Engineering",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1. Assist QP(S) in the site supervision of civil/structural works and geotechnical works.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>2. Manage a team of Site Supervisors (SS) on site to ensure that all works comply fully with regulatory and Client's requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>3. Work closely with Project Management Team, QP(S), QP(D), Client, Contractors and local Authorities to ensure successful and timely completion of the project.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>4. Attend regular site progress meetings to resolve site issues.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>5. Carry out regular site inspections on Contractor’s works to ensure site supervision quality &amp; site safety.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>6. Review Contractor’s submissions to ensure compliance with regulatory and Client's requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>7. Ensure Contractor’s works is carried out in accordance with approved designs and drawings.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>8. Identify any non-conformance of Contractor's works on site and to follow up with Contractor to ensure rectification of non-conformance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>9. Ensure proper and up-to-date site documentation for on-going and completed works.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirement</strong></u></p>\n<p>1. Registered with IES/ ACES.</p>\n<p>2. Conversant with BCA Regulations, maintenance of systematic site records, government contract documents and meet BCA reporting requirements.</p>",
